No. 155. The Federal Constitution.

The Swz'ssers, which are those people whom the ancients called Helvetians, have their habitations in the highest moun— taines of sura, of Valesz'a, and S. Godar: and are naturally valiant, warlike, and rude, and for the sterilitie of the country, rather shepheards than tillers of the ground. They have bene in times past under the subjection of the Dukes of Austria, whose jurisdiction they have shaken off many yeares since. They govern themselves, without any dependencie of either Emperoms, Kings or other Princes. They are devided into thirteene communalties‚ which they call Cantons‚ each of them being severally governed by their particular Magistrates, lawes and ordinances. They hold their Councell every yeare, or more often if occasion require, wherein they dispute of uni- versall affastes, their assemblies and meetings being not subject to certaintie of places, but referred as best pleaseth the ³ Deputies of every Canton.
